sys_properties.value:
REQUIRED FILE DATA FOR REGULATORY AFFAIRS

 

Due to complaint audit and reporting requirements, supporting documentation must be attached in ETS after quality review has been completed.  Below is a list of documents required for all cases (as applicable). *Enter Yes/No/NA/Attachment to indicate which documents are included in your file. 

 

  • Use No when the document should be available but we are unable to locate it (e.g. MLI letter). 

Use NA if the document is not applicable to your complaint or if there is no document. Use Attach if the required elements are included in the attachment file to the resolution letter. If the document is an attachment to your response, you do not need to also include it as a screenprint. 

*All information is inclusive of any archived information.

 

*No Audit File is required on PCA cases in which no new information is provided (i.e. the DOI is only requesting clarification of claim payment previously sent)

 

INCLUDED?

*Yes/No/ NA/Attach

REQUIRED FILE DATA

 

Email to manager/regional director on Risk Management – Escalation Driver issues, if applicable.

 

Does your response letter address all the agency’s requirements/requests and complainant’s issues?

 

Screen Print of Due Date Calculation/Ack Decision Tree Tool

*Not required for CANSS or when specific due date is provided on the DOI complaint letter*

*Required only for PCAs (when a specific due date is not provided on the regulatory complaint letter), and instances where the Triage calculation is inaccurate*

 

Screen Print of search in Matter Management (T360) LCRA tracking database OR Screen Print of search in Matter Management Report spreadsheet on our SharePoint

 

*ONLY required if there is an indication, threat, or allegation of legal action in complaint.

 

(Your screen print should only include a record related to your issue, if your search returns unrelated cases black out the info or use a screen print with no records returned)

 

Eligibility Screen prints showing:*

 

  • Verification of funding**  (if ASO screen print showing ERISA or Non-ERISA always required)
  • Situs**
  • Member’s SSN and/or Alt ID**
  • Member’s name and covered dependent(s) **
  • Member’s address**
  • Group number**
  • Group name**
  • Dates of coverage
  • Product**
  • Product code/set number
  • Legal Entity**
  • COB screen prints showing effective dates and who is primary/secondary, if applicable

 

*Not required when claims spreadsheet is used for multiple enrollees.

 

*Items marked with double asterick (**) are not required if ETS auto-populates correct information using Member Look-Up button

 

*CDX screenshots are not required on Exchange cases only

 

Claim Screen prints showing:**

 

  • Claim processing details for initial processing and any adjustments, if applicable.*
  • The processor ID or name, if applicable.  This information is applicable if it’s important as to who processed the claim (i.e. system or manual processing).
  • Check number and date issued, if applicable.*
  • Date processed, if applicable.
  • Explanation of all reason codes, if applicable.*
  • Any notes screens related to claim issue, if applicable.
  • Notification screen print including details of notification, if applicable.
  • Contracted rates or R&C/UCR rates, MNRP, or Shared Savings discounts, if applicable.

 

**Not required when claims spreadsheet is used for multiple enrollees.

 

Provider Screen prints showing:* **

 

  • Provider’s TIN, if applicable. 
  • Provider’s Name, if applicable. 
  • Provider’s Address, if applicable. 
  • Provider’s network status, if applicable.
  • Effective dates of contract for various products, if applicable.

 

*Not necessary to include if the provider information is included in your enclosures or in your audit file unless your issue is specifically regarding one of the above.

 

**Not required when claims spreadsheet is used for multiple providers.

 

COC/SPD/SOB screen prints:**

 

  • COC/SPD/SOB cover page, if applicable. *
  • Applicable COC/SPD/SOB pages showing related benefits or requirements, if applicable.*
  • Effective date of the COC/SPD/SOB, if applicable.
  • Other screens providing benefit information, if applicable. (IBAAG/PASS/CDX/Web C.S.A./Universe/YODA)

 

*Not necessary to include if this information is included in your enclosures or in another document already included in your audit file.

 

**Not required when claims spreadsheet is used for multiple enrollees.

 

***COC screenshots are not required on Exchange cases only

 

Correspondence screen prints showing:**

 

  • System generated letters, if applicable. 
  • Appeals received, if applicable. 
  • Response to appeals, if applicable.
  • Letters sent authorizing or denying services, if applicable.
  • Written documentation received pertinent to case, if applicable. 
  • Written documentation issued pertinent to case, if applicable.
  • System screen prints of places the correspondence is obtained. For example: ETS, Pega, ICUE, etc. (This list is not all inclusive)

 

*For large electronic documents, advocate can attach the FLN to audit file in place of all pages of the document. This can include the ORS/UNET/ETS screen print, or documented FLN, so document can be retrieved in the future. 

 

*Not necessary to include if this information is included in your enclosures or in another document already included in your audit file.

 

**Not required when claims spreadsheet is used for multiple enrollees.

 

**ICUE screen prints are not required for Care Core notifications unless the ICUE notification affected claim processing and/or affects outcome of the case.

 

**ETS screenprints for appeals only requires a screenshot of the search results or top section of the appeal unless there are issues referenced in the comments or impacts the outcome of the case

 

 

ORS/Comm Events/Other call documentation screen prints showing:*

 

  • Any related records not included above, as applicable.
  • Record created for your ETS case.
  • Any calls received, if applicable.
  • Any calls placed, if applicable.

 

*Not necessary to include if the information is included in your enclosures or in another document already included in your audit file.

 

*Not required for a multiple member provider complaint when it does not impact the outcome and is not being requested by the regulator.

 

Reference screen prints showing:*

 

  • Internal policies, if applicable.
  • CPT/HCPCS/ICD-9 code descriptions, if applicable.
  • Modifier definitions, if applicable.
  • Medical policies or reimbursement policies, if applicable.
  • Administrative policies, if applicable.

 

*Not necessary to include if the information is included in your enclosures or in another document already included in your audit file.

 

Internal Communications screen prints showing:

 

  • Emails pertinent to case, if applicable.
  • Office communicator discussions pertinent to case, if applicable.

 

 

Explanation of Benefits screen prints:

 

  • Explanations of Benefits or Provider Remittance Advice, if applicable.  Not necessary to include if included in your enclosure file. (Also not necessary if enclosing a claims spreadsheet instead of EOBs)

 

*All above information is inclusive of any archived information
